WEBVTT

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:33.896
Eventually, she started
a prototypically introverted project:

00:03:33.920 --> 00:03:35.776
writing a book about introverts.

00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:38.496
SC: I felt like I was working
on an odd project

00:03:38.520 --> 00:03:41.120
that was hard to talk about
at dinner parties.

00:03:41.760 --> 00:03:44.416
AG: Well, it also makes it hard
to go to dinner parties.

00:03:44.440 --> 00:03:45.976
SC: (Laughs)

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.696
(Music)

00:03:49.720 --> 00:03:51.456
AG: Susan's book, "Quiet,"

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:54.856
ignited a national conversation
about the neglected role of introverts

00:03:54.880 --> 00:03:56.736
in work and life.

00:03:56.760 --> 00:03:59.336
She learned that,
like all the major traits,

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:02.376
introversion-extraversion
has roots in your physiology,